'''Betty Swords''' was an American [[cartoonist]] whose work appeared in the ''[[Saturday Evening Post]]'', ''[[Redbook]]'', ''[[Good Housekeeping]]'', ''[[Ladies Home Journal]]'', ''[[Kiplinger's Personal Finance|Changing Times]]'', and others, usually using her own gags but sometimes from other writers. She also wrote gags for ''[[Dennis the Menace (U.S. comics)|Dennis the Menace]]'' and others. Her humorous writing appeared in ''[[McCall’s]]'', ''[[Modern Maturity]]'', ''[[Christian Science Monitor]]'', and others.
Swords was raised in [[Oakland, California]], earned her [[Bachelor of Fine Arts]] at [[University of California, Berkeley]] and did graduate work the [[San Francisco Academy of Advertising Art]].
